  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Roles__IT_Architects&quot; name=&quot;XE_Roles__IT_Architects&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This role set lists the IT architects, which do IT Architecture; the primary roles for the Unified Architecture Method.&#xD;
    There are&amp;nbsp;normally three primary&amp;nbsp;roles defined by the scope of their responsibilities within the enterprise,&#xD;
    namely the Enterprise Architect who typically works for the CIO, the Domain or Business Line Architects who typically&#xD;
    work for the VPs of the business line or business domain, and the Business Unit and Project IT architects responsible&#xD;
    for business unit or IT project architectures. Depending upon the size of the organization, there may be just an&#xD;
    enterprise architect, or there may be an enterprise architect, plus domain architects for each business domain within&#xD;
    the enterprise, plus business unit and project architects.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_UAM__IT_architects&quot; name=&quot;XE_UAM__IT_architects&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
